# Git workflow

## Branches

| Branch | Role |
|---|---|
| `staging` | **Development integration branch** ‚Äî all feature work and orchestrator-verified commits land here |
| `main` | **Protected production branch** ‚Äî release line only; not for day-to-day development |

- Feature work happens on **`staging`** (Lane S serial) or isolated `orchestrator/<TASK-ID>` branches (Lane P), merged into `staging` after verify.
- **`main` is protected on GitHub.** Agents and orchestrator runs must **never push to `main`** until an explicit release promotion workflow exists.
- Promoting `staging` ‚Üí `main` is operator-only (release); not part of routine task orchestration.

## Commit messages (Conventional Commits)

Subject ‚â§72 chars, imperative mood, **scoped**. **Task commits must link a work item** in square brackets ‚Äî see `07-issue-commit-linking.mdc`.

```
feat(<scope>)[#123]: <imperative summary>
fix(<scope>)[#123]: <summary>
chore(<scope>)[#123]: <summary>
refactor(<scope>)[#123]: <summary>
docs(<scope>)[#123]: <summary>
test(<scope>)[#123]: <summary>
ci(<scope>)[#123]: <summary>
build(<scope>)[#123]: <summary>
perf(<scope>)[#123]: <summary>
```

Use `[#N]` when the task is on GitHub Issues. The commit body must include `fixes #N` to auto-close the issue on merge to `main`. Subtasks under an epic also close parent Features via `fixes #<parent>` on the **final in-scope child** only ‚Äî see `07-issue-commit-linking.mdc`.

**Allowed scopes**: `repo`, `ci`, `api`, `worker`, `web`, `marketing`, `db`, `types`, `utils`, `config`, `docs`, `workspaces`, `integrations`, `repositories`, `pipelines`, `runs`, `webhooks`, `auth`, `billing`, `sse`, `insights`, `onboarding`, `ce`, `infra`, `deps`

(`db` = Drizzle schema/migrations ¬∑ `types` = `packages/types` ¬∑ `config` = `packages/config` edition/flags)

Session memory (`.cursor/skills/agent-memory/`) is **gitignored** ‚Äî local working notes only. Verifiers post outcomes to GitHub issues; never commit session files.

## Commit rules

- **Never** `git add .` or `git add -A`. Always stage explicit paths.
- One task = **one implementation commit**. No session memory commits.
- Never amend commits that have been pushed.

## Push policy

**Never push** unless the user explicitly asks. Local commits only.

**Never push to `main` on GitHub** ‚Äî not even when the user asks for a push during development. The only valid remote target for task work is **`staging`** (or a Lane P task branch).

## Examples

```bash
# GOOD ‚Äî GitHub issue work
git add apps/api/src/routes/webhooks/github.ts \
        apps/api/src/routes/webhooks/github.test.ts
git commit -m "feat(webhooks)[#12]: verify GitHub HMAC signature on ingest

fixes #12"

# BAD ‚Äî blanket staging
git add .

# BAD ‚Äî no scope / no task key
git commit -m "added webhooks"
```
